PART 12: PROJECTIVE LINE PG(1,q) AND FORBIDDEN VALUES
======================================================================
  Forbidden value counts:
    n=3: 0 forbidden (both odd values 1,3 achieved)
    n=4: 0 forbidden (all 3 odd values 1,3,5 achieved)
    n=5: 1 forbidden (7 is not achieved)
    n=6: 4 forbidden ({7, 21, 35, 39})
    n=7: 18 forbidden

  Forbidden count sequence: 0, 0, 1, 4, 18
  Differences: 0, 1, 3, 14
  Ratios: -, inf, 4.0, 4.5

  Note: 0, 0, 1, 4, 18 ~ 0, 0, 1, 4, 18
  Check Catalan: C_0=1, C_1=1, C_2=2, C_3=5, C_4=14. No match.
  Check Bell: B_0=1, B_1=1, B_2=2, B_3=5, B_4=15. No match.

  18 = 2 * 3^2
  Could the forbidden values grow like 2 * 3^(n-5)?
    n=5: 1, n=6: 4 (would predict 2), n=7: 18 (would predict 6). No.

  More likely: forbidden fraction ~ 1/5 at n=7 (18/95 = 0.189)
  At n=6: 4/23 = 0.174
  At n=5: 1/8 = 0.125
  Increasing slowly... might approach some limit?

